# K8s-Setup-guide
This project demonstrates the setup of a Kubernetes cluster from scratch, including control plane and worker node configuration, etcd, kube-apiserver, networking, TLS certificates, and workload deployment. It highlights hands-on experience with Kubernetes architecture, Linux, troubleshooting, and cluster management.

# ☸️ Kubernetes Setup Guide

A comprehensive, beginner-friendly guide to understanding and configuring Kubernetes from the ground up. This repository covers Kubernetes architecture, core components, object management, networking, namespaces, deployments, and essential `kubectl` commands with practical examples.

## 📖 Topics Covered

* Kubernetes Architecture
* ETCD
* Kube API Server
* Kube Controller Manager
* Kube Scheduler
* Kubelet
* Kube Proxy
* Pods
* ReplicaSets & Replication Controllers
* Deployments
* Services (ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer)
* Namespaces & Resource Quotas
* Imperative vs Declarative Management
* YAML Manifests
* Kubectl Commands & Best Practices

## 🛠️ Prerequisites

* Basic Linux knowledge
* Docker or a Container Runtime
* Kubernetes Cluster (Minikube, kubeadm, Kind, or K3s)
* kubectl CLI

